aught politics of the post-independence Arab world. The Sultan's Communists contributes to the growing literature on Jews in the modern Middle East and provides a new history of twentieth-century Jewish Morocco.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJewish communistsxHistoryy20th centuryzMorocco. 0aJewish communistszMoroccoxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewsxPolitics and governmentzMorocco. 0aJewszMoroccoxPolitics and governmenty20th century. 0aNationalism and communismzMoroccoxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aArab nationalism.  aCold War.  aColonialism.  aCommunism.  aIsrael.  aJews.  aMorocco.  aVichy Regime.  aYears of Lead.  aZionism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishz978311070477808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781503614147?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503614147423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503614147/original  a978-3-11-069218-1  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070477-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020